The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Dec. 3: The Left Front will table a motion in the Assembly tomorrow to condemn Thursdays Trinamul vandalism. 

 Left Front chief whip Syed Mohammed Mosih said the six front legislators injured in the Trinamul assault will introduce the motion.

 Calcutta: An oil tanker ran over two pedestrians under the new flyover on Diamond Harbour Road and hit a cyclist on Sunday evening. The cyclist has been admitted to SSKM Hospital. Police said the truck driver has been held.

 Durgapur: Coal India has decided to install automatic alarms to sound an alert in case of a mine disaster. Six miners were killed when a portion of a colliery in Andal caved in. Coal India chairman P.S. Bhattacharya, who visited the mishap site on Saturday, made the announcement.

 Andal: Two Trinamul panchayat leaders and four partymen have been arrested for allegedly snatching a necklace from Sujata Bauri, the chief of the CPM-run Madanpur village panchayat. Ghanashyam Diashi, 45, a member of the Andal panchayat samiti, and Bapi Mondal, 40, of the Madanpur village body are in custody.




